# Training Context — ÖTILLÖ Swimrun Utö 2026

## Goal Race

**Event:** ÖTILLÖ Swimrun Utö — World Series distance  
**Date:** June 6, 2026  
**Location:** Utö, Stockholm Archipelago, Sweden  
**Link:** https://otilloswimrun.com/races/uto-sweden/  
**Format:** Team of 2 (racing with a friend)

### Race Profile
| | Distance |
|---|---|
| Total | 32 170 m |
| Run | 27 660 m |
| Swim | 4 510 m |
| Elevation | 237 m |

**Estimated finish time:** ~5–6 hours  
**Goal:** Complete the race together — finishing is the priority, not speed.

### Cut-offs to be aware of
- TIME 3 at Utö Harbour: **14:20**
- TIME 5 at Utö North: **15:50**

---

## Race Conditions & Terrain

### Running
- Rocky granite islands in the Baltic Sea archipelago
- Technical trails: slippery, uneven, rough terrain
- Pine forests, coastal paths, some elevation gain

### Swimming
- Open water in the Baltic Sea (low salinity)
- Cold water — wetsuit required and will be used
- Swimming technique: **arms-only with hand paddles**; legs are lifted by a pull buoy; running shoes stay on in the water

---

## Athlete Profile

**Training start date:** May 11, 2026 (26 days to race)

### Recent Performance
- **May 9, 2026 — Half Marathon:** Finished in **1h35** — went well overall, but experienced **cramps in the final stretch**.

### Known Limiters / Notes
- Cramping under sustained effort (likely hydration/electrolyte or pacing related)
- Need to practice swim-to-run and run-to-swim transitions in race gear (wetsuit on/off, paddles, buoy)
- Cold water acclimatisation beneficial given race conditions
- Rocky terrain running practice recommended (trail shoes essential)

---

## Equipment
- Wetsuit
- Hand paddles
- Pull buoy (to lift legs during swimming)
- Trail running shoes (worn during swimming too)

---

## Training Philosophy
- **Completion over performance** — the goal is to finish strong with a teammate, not race the clock
- With ~4 weeks to race day, the focus should be on race-specific conditioning, injury prevention, and confidence-building rather than peak fitness gains
- Key areas: swim endurance (arms-only), run endurance on technical terrain, brick sessions (swim→run), cramp prevention strategies

